  <h3 align="center" style="color:#000000">Mission Statement</h3>

  <p align="justify">The mission of this site is to demonstrate proficiency in both Ruby, Ruby on Rails and
    cloud administration. In this case the cloud is Amazon Web Services.</p>

  <p align="justify">The main reason for employers to login is to demonstrate both
    web site access control, user authentication and email address verification,
    in combination with the mySQL database storage of users.</p>

  <p align="justify">Used in this application were, Ruby, Ruby on Rails with a remote cloud hosted
    mySQL database implementation using RDS on AWS. This means your development system and your
    production system can be hosted in a common cloud location.</p>

  <p align="justify">The gems used in this application are aws-sdk, aws-ses, bcrypt, bootstrap-sass,
    bootstrap-will_paginate, coffee-rails, faker, figaro, guard-minitest, jbuilder, jquery-rails,
    json, mini_backtrace, minitest-reporters, mysql3, rails,
    rspec, sass-rails, sdoc, spring, turbolinks, uglifier, web-consol, and will_paginate</p>

